article.headline: UTEP 108, Texas State 60
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Stefon Jackson scored 23 points to lead six players in double figures as Texas-El Paso defeated Texas State 108-60 Tuesday night. Darren Clarke scored 18 points and Maurice Thomas, Kevin Henderson and Dale Vanwright each scored 13 points for the Miners (6-6). Jeremy Sampson added 10. Thomas also had 10 rebounds. Malik Alvin had 11 assists. UTEP got 65 of its points from the bench, led by Clarke. Brent Holder led Texas State with 14 points. Antwoine Blanchard added 12 and Dylan Moseley scored 10. UTEP led 44-25 at the half after shooting 58 percent from the field to only 19 percent for Texas State (4-7). Texas State picked up the pace some in the second half, but the Miners didn't falter. While Texas State was shooting 38 percent from the field, UTEP shot 57 percent.
